cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SE

This paper discusses the security and usability of Tor onion services, which involves topics related to computer security (cs.CR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybercrime (cs.CY), and software engineering (cs.SE). The focus on user perception and behavior also suggests a potential fit with the sub-categories of cs.CY and cs.HC.
